{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868336202,"sessionID":"ses_28600caadffeyFoPa3o4lehoYR","part":{"id":"prt_d79ff8f00001Sj3VUGqvJDeuJS","messageID":"msg_d79ff85e70016EUDtiAbua0CuP","sessionID":"ses_28600caadffeyFoPa3o4lehoYR","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_764ac3f2a69e461abec86233","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/tasks.md","content":"# AR-022 — CLI Publish Command Tasks\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation & Models ✓\n\n- [x] **T1.1** Define `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with publish-related fields\n  - Fields: `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`, `agent_endpoint`, `version`, `region`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/metadata_models.py`\n  - Verify: Model validates correctly with test fixtures\n\n- [x] **T1.2** Implement `MetadataService.load_metadata()` and `save_metadata()`\n  - Support multiple metadata file names: `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n  - Verify: Loads/saves metadata correctly in test workspace\n\n- [x] **T1.3** Add publish-related CLI options to `PublishRuntime`\n  - Options: `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `region`, `cloud_provider`, `provider`, `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Options are accepted and passed through runtime methods\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Core Runtime Implementation ✓\n\n- [x] **T2.1** Implement `PublishRuntime.publish()` method\n  - Load metadata, prepare image, delegate to provider, update metadata\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns `Dict[str, Any]` with agent info\n\n- [x] **T2.2** Implement `_prepare_image_for_publishing()` dispatcher\n  - Route to `_prepare_local_image()` or `_prepare_cloud_image()` based on `metadata.build_mode`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct routing logic\n\n- [x] **T2.3** Implement `_prepare_local_image()` for local build mode\n  - Validate `image_url` is provided\n  - Push image to registry using `DockerService.push_image()` if credentials available\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns `image_url`, pushes image when credentials provided\n\n- [x] **T2.4** Implement `_prepare_cloud_image()` for cloud build mode\n  - Construct image URL from `cloud_provider`, `agent_name`, `version`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns formatted image URL string\n\n- [x] **T2.5** Implement `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` for AgentCube provider\n  - Create `AgentCubeProvider` instance\n  - Deploy `AgentRuntime` CR with required fields: `workloadManagerURL`, `routerURL`, readiness probe\n  - Generate `session_id`, `agent_id`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns dict with `status`, `agent_name`, `namespace`, `session_id`, `agent_id`\n\n- [x] **T2.6** Implement `_publish_k8s()` for standard K8s provider\n  - Create `KubernetesProvider` instance\n  - Deploy `Deployment` + `Service` (optionally `NodePort`)\n  - Validate `node_port` range (30000-32767)\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns dict with deployment info\n\n- [x] **T2.7** Implement `_update_publish_metadata()` to persist publish results\n  - Update: `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`, `agent_endpoint`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Metadata file updated after publish\n\n- [x] **T2.8** Implement `_generate_session_id()` helper\n  - Generate 32-character alphanumeric string using `secrets.choice()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns unique ID on each call\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Provider Services ✓\n\n- [x] **T3.1** Implement `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()`\n  - Create/replace `AgentRuntime` CR in K8s\n  - Handle 409 conflict (update existing)\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verify: CR created/updated in cluster\n\n- [x] **T3.2** Implement `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name()` for K8s naming rules\n  - Lowercase, replace non-alphanumeric with `-`, max 63 chars\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Produces valid K8s resource names\n\n- [x] **T3.3** Implement `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` for standard K8s deployment\n  - Create `Deployment`, `Service` (ClusterIP or NodePort)\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Resources created in cluster\n\n- [x] **T3.4** Add error handling for missing K8s config\n  - Try kubeconfig, then in-cluster config\n  - Raise `RuntimeError` with helpful message if both fail\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`, `k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Clear error message when K8s unavailable\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: CLI Integration ✓\n\n- [x] **T4.1** Add `publish` command to CLI with Typer\n  - All options from T1.3 as `@app.command()` parameters\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: `agentcube publish --help` shows all options\n\n- [x] **T4.2** Implement CLI progress UI for publish\n  - Use `rich.progress` spinner during publish\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Spinner displays during operation\n\n- [x] **T4.3** Format and display publish results\n  - Show: `Agent ID`, `Endpoint`, `Namespace`, `Provider`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Output is clear and readable\n\n- [x] **T4.4** Implement consistent error handling\n  - Use `_handle_error()` helper with verbose traceback option\n  - Exit code 1 on failure\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Errors display clearly, verbose mode shows traceback\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Validation & Edge Cases\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Validate `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` are present for `agentcube` provider\n  - Check metadata or environment variables\n  - Raise `ValueError` with helpful message if missing\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Clear error when URLs missing\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Validate `node_port` range (30000-32767) for K8s provider\n  - Already implemented in `_publish_k8s()`, add CLI-level validation\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Rejects invalid ports before runtime call\n\n- [ ] **T5.3** Handle existing AgentRuntime CR gracefully (update vs create)\n  - Already implemented via 409 handling in `AgentCubeProvider`\n  - Add logging to indicate update vs create\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Logs indicate whether CR was created or updated\n\n- [ ] **T5.4** Handle image push failures gracefully\n  - Catch `DockerService` exceptions, re-raise with context\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Clear error message on push failure\n\n- [ ] **T5.5** Validate metadata file exists before publish\n  - Check for `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Early error if metadata missing\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Testing\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Unit test `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()`\n  - Test with/without `image_url`, with/without credentials\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct image URL returned, push called when expected\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Unit test `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image()`\n  - Test various `cloud_provider`, `version` combinations\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct image URL format\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Unit test `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()`\n  - Mock `AgentCubeProvider`, verify CR spec\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct provider call, session_id generated\n\n- [ ] **T6.4** Unit test `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()`\n  - Mock `KubernetesProvider`, verify deployment params\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct provider call, node_port validated\n\n- [ ] **T6.5** Integration test: publish to K8s (mock cluster)\n  - Use `kind` or `kindless` K8s cluster\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_publish_integration.py`\n  - Verify: CR/deployment created, metadata updated\n\n- [ ] **T6.6** CLI test: `agentcube publish --help`\n  - Verify all options documented\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_cli.py`\n  - Verify: Help text accurate\n\n- [ ] **T6.7** Error case: missing `workload_manager_url`\n  - Verify clear error message\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: `ValueError` raised with helpful message\n\n- [ ] **T6.8** Error case: invalid `node_port`\n  - Verify validation rejects out-of-range ports\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: `ValueError` for invalid ports\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Documentation & Cleanup\n\n- [ ] **T7.1** Add docstrings to all public methods\n  - Follow Google/NumPy style\n  - File: All publish-related files\n  - Verify: `help()` displays correctly\n\n- [ ] **T7.2** Add type hints to all functions\n  - Use `typing` module for complex types\n  - File: All publish-related files\n  - Verify: `mypy` passes\n\n- [ ] **T7.3** Update README with publish command examples\n  - Show `agentcube publish --provider=agentcube` and `--provider=k8s`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/README.md`\n  - Verify: Examples are copy-paste runnable\n\n- [ ] **T7.4** Add troubleshooting section for common publish errors\n  - Missing URLs, image push failures, K8s config issues\n  - File: `cmd/cli/README.md` or `docs/cli/publish.md`\n  - Verify: Clear resolutions for each error\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `PublishRuntime` class fully implemented with all methods\n2. ✅ CLI `publish` command accepts all required options\n3. ✅ Two providers supported: `agentcube` (CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service)\n4. ✅ Image preparation works for both `local` and `cloud` build modes\n5. ✅ Metadata updated with publish results (`agent_id`, `session_id`, etc.)\n6. ✅ Error handling provides clear, actionable messages\n7. ⏳ Unit tests cover all publish runtime methods\n8. ⏳ Integration test validates end-to-end publish flow\n9. ⏳ Documentation includes examples and troubleshooting\n\n---\n\n**Notes:**\n- Stage ST-3 is marked complete: runtime, providers, and CLI are implemented\n- Remaining work: comprehensive testing (Phase 6) and documentation (Phase 7)\n- Edge case validation (Phase 5) partially complete, needs CLI-level validation\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py\">\nERROR [52:28] Object of type \"None\" cannot be called\nERROR [61:23] \"ConfigException\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [58:24] \"load_kube_config\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [60:24] \"load_kube_config\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [64:27] \"ConfigException\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [63:24] \"load_incluster_config\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [73:30] \"CoreV1Api\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [76:18] Cannot access attribute \"status\" for class \"Exception\"\n  Attribute \"status\" is unknown\nERROR [77:34] \"CoreV1Api\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [78:36] \"V1Namespace\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [79:37] \"V1ObjectMeta\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [119:20] \"V1EnvVar\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [156:18] Cannot access attribute \"status\" for class \"Exception\"\n  Attribute \"status\" is unknown\nERROR [185:20]